  "texts": [
    "When the cross-domain datasets are used for training, they are fully used for that purpose (and none of them is used for tuning nor testing).",
    "For each experiment, we train five models to test on the five different folds of AuSTR, and finally report the average performance of the five models.",
    "To train our stance models, we fine-tuned BERT Devlin et al. (2018), following recent studies that adopted transformer-based models for stance detection Alhindi et al.",
    "2021) as it was shown to achieve better performance on most of the stance datasets adopted in our work Alhindi et al. (2021).",
    "All models were trained with a maximum of 25 epochs where 5 was set as an early stopping threshold."
